  "texts": [
    "However, these software applications have been found to have certain limitations in terms of effectively integrating graphic, algebraic and tabular representations, as well as providing a dynamic learning environment and ease of use, when compared to GeoGebra (Birgin & Yazıcı, 2021).",
    "GeoGebra is a notable example of a freely available, open-source, dynamic learning environment that facilitates exploration of the relationship between algebra and geometry while visualizing mathematical concepts.",
    "This software incorporates the features of both computer algebra systems and DGS, rendering it suitable for use across various educational levels, ranging from elementary to higher education (Hohenwarter & Jones, 2007).",
    "Moreover, GeoGebra has a user-friendly interface that facilitates students' ability to establish connections between geometric, algebraic and numerical representations.",
    "It is important to note that GeoGebra is freely accessible without any license or permission restrictions and can be downloaded from the authorized website (www.geogebra.org) for installation on personal computers and laptops, as well as iPads and smartphone devices."
  ],
